cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it introduces a machine learning pipeline for making predictions based on online user behavior. It also uses techniques such as model calibration, which are commonly used in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the pipeline is designed to create website- and task-specific models without knowing anything about the structure of the website, which is a common problem in information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with online user behavior, which is a social phenomenon. 

It could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as Bloom filters, which are used in the pipeline, are commonly used in cryptography and security. 

Finally, it could belong to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as it deals with online user behavior and creating website-specific models, which are important aspects of human-computer interaction.
